            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Rep_Post_Edits_23.png",
            "title": "<strong>Lightbound</strong>",
            "text": "<p>April features David Dalglish's dark fantasy about immortal siblings bound by an ancient oath—until one brother breaks it, bringing divine power to mortal hands. The box showcases Dynamite Coffee's perfectly balanced blend mirroring the story's interplay of light and dark, Gnat and Bee's peach-ginger white tea, and Raaka's decadent Double Dark drinking chocolate. Plus, enjoy Strange Syrup's Sizzling Cinnamon, infused with warming spices that transform everything it touches<br/><br/></p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_YPTMxG": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Rep_Post_Edits_1080_x_1080_px_4.png",
            "title": "<strong>Into The Void</strong>",
            "text": "<p>This March, journey into \"Grave Empire\" by Richard Swan, where three argonauts race to decode an end-of-days prophecy. The box showcases Methodical Coffee's versatile Play Nice blend, Little Woods Tea's complex Fireside Elderberry Black, and Moka Origins' ethically sourced 72% Deliciously Dark Drinking Chocolate, plus an upcycled adventure-ready bag from Alchemy Goods crafted from recycled bike tires.<br/><br/></p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_r8wzfR": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Rep_Post_Edits_1080_x_1080_px_1.png",
            "title": "<strong>The Fates</strong>",
            "text": "<p>February brings \"Daughter of Chaos,\" where outcast Danae discovers her extraordinary power while navigating a world of mythic beasts and treacherous alliances. This box features eTreehouse Chocolate's decadent 72% drinking chocolate, Brewtus Roasters' bold house blend, and Felicity Loft's classic Alaskan Breakfast Tea. The tea towel reminding us that greatness often emerges from humble beginnings.<br/><br/></p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        }
